  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated Support to Link Agricultural Production to the Prevention of Malnutrition in Rural Rwanda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Integrated Support to Link Agricultural Production to the Prevention of Malnutrition program in Rwanda is built on Concern&#x2019;s prevention of under nutrition (PUN) model and complements the Government of Rwanda Joint Action Plan for Eliminating Malnutrition (December 2011). The PUN model is a multi-sectorial, nutrition-Sensitive approach which aims at addressing the four dimensions of food security (availability, access, utilization and stability), which are embedded in the household food security part of the UNICEF conceptual framework.

The strategies employed by the PUN model are:
&#x2022; Increasing access to nutritious food;
&#x2022; Improving access to nutrition information for behaviour change; 
&#x2022; Supporting delivery of quality health and nutrition services through the community health structure in Rwanda and also at the health centre level;
&#x2022; Promoting women&#x2019;s empowerment to have equal say in the production, use and consumption of agricultural products at household level; and 
&#x2022; Constructive, evidence-based engagement at national level to support the shift towards preventative interventions that require the combined support of MoH and MINAGRI</narrative>
  </description>
